Synopsis: Domain API Test Plan for Activities GET and POST Requests in Acceptance Environment

Introduction:
This test plan outlines the testing approach for the Activities API in the acceptance environment. The API allows users to perform GET and POST requests related to activities within the domain. The primary objective of this test plan is to ensure the functionality, performance, and security of the API in the acceptance environment before it is deployed to production.

Test Scope:
The test scope includes comprehensive testing of the Activities API in the acceptance environment for both GET and POST requests. It covers various scenarios, including valid and invalid inputs, error handling, performance, and security aspects.

Test Environment:
The acceptance environment should be a replica of the production environment with realistic data. The following components should be in place:

Acceptance server: A dedicated server to host the API in the acceptance environment.
